From 0f41a82c490e60a9947c1db2091901e9bd49c57f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matei Dobrescu <contact@md0.ro>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 03:00:55 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] Miyoo Mini (Allium CFW) port integration hooks (mmx_miyoo
 module)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wires the self-contained mmx_miyoo module (mmx_miyoo.c/h/cmake, shipped
separately) into the engine, enabled by -DALIS_MIYOO_ALLIUM=ON:

- CMakeLists: ALIS_MIYOO_ALLIUM option; on Miyoo include src/mmx_miyoo.cmake
  (static SDL2, no audio/video/joystick backends) instead of
  find_package(SDL2), build src/mmx_miyoo.c, skip the standalone emu2149
  lib (it overrides CMAKE_C_FLAGS and breaks cross builds)
- sys.c: route SDL_GetKeyboardState/SDL_GetModState to the evdev-fed shim;
  OR the Miyoo button bits into sys_joy_compose; audio locks go to the
  module's pump mutex; sys_fopen/sys_fexists resolve paths case-
  insensitively instead of strlower (which breaks on the device's
  case-sensitive /mnt/SDCARD — every game resource open failed, leaving
  a black screen with an idle VM)
- opcodes.c: csload resolves the script path the same way
- sys_sdl2.c: init without video/joystick/audio backends; poll evdev
  buttons each cycle; present frames via /dev/fb0 instead of the SDL
  renderer; no mouse cursor; log why the VM loop exited (NDEBUG mutes
  signals_info). Audio keeps the SDL-style callback but is pumped by the
  module's /dev/dsp thread — SDL's dsp backend opens via open64 which
  Allium's libpadsp.so shim does not intercept, and with no device the
  pump still runs the callback so the music engine advances

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
